
                                            The NUM had planned to serve a 48-hour notice to the Chamber of Mines on Monday.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - The National Union of Mineworkers (NUM) has delayed a plan to serve a strike notice in the coal sector after some companies revised their wage offers. The NUM had planned to serve a 48-hour notice to the Chamber of Mines on Monday. It says it will first present the offers to it's members before deciding on a way forward. The NUM's Livhuwani Mamburu: "Our members have mandated the NUM to postpone the strike notice until tomorrow to allow the coal companies to present the new offer."